<title>USA: Berkshire $500 mln notes filing effective.</title>
<headline>Berkshire $500 mln notes filing effective.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1996-11-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>Berkshire Hathaway Inc said Friday its filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission involving the sale of $500 million of its 1.00 pct senior exchangeable notes due December 2, 2001 have become effective.</p>
<p>Berkshire, through which Omaha investor Warren Buffett holds investments in prominent U.S. companies, said the notes would be exchangeable for Salomon Inc common stock upon maturity or redemption.</p>
<p>Berkshire said the transaction is expected to be completed on December 2.</p>
